post_text: There are still a couple more days to apply!
shared_text:
Chris Patterson Memorial Foundation
April 10 at 12:51 AM ¬∑

Who do you know that you can share, tag, or message with this post? Applications must be mailed and received by April 16, 2020. So don't delay!

This year's high schools include: West Aurora, East Aurora, Batavia, Geneva, and Kaneland. Please help us get the word out to seniors from these high schools that have participated in the Performing Arts (Band, Choir, Orchestra, Drama or Stage Crew).

Information on how to apply is available at: https://chrispattersonmemorial.org/performing-arts-award/

In lieu of teacher signatures on the Awards Endorsement Form, students may email their instructor asking for confirmation of their participation and then print and include a copy of the teacher's response email. If there are questions, please email us at: hello@ChrisPattersonMemorial.org

shared_text:
Chris Patterson Memorial Foundation
March 30 at 9:53 PM ¬∑

The deadline for this year's Performing Arts Awards is quickly approaching! Please help us reach seniors from West Aurora, East Aurora, Batavia, Geneva, and Kaneland High Schools.

Especially this year's new schools - Geneva High School Geneva School District 304, Geneva Community High School and Kaneland High School Kaneland School District 302, Kaneland High School, Kaneland High School Athletics & Activities, Kaneland Performing Arts Boosters.

Please encourage seniors from these high schools that have participated in the Performing Arts (Band, Choir, Orchestra, Drama or Stage Crew) to apply. Applications must be mailed and received by April 6, 2020. So don't delay!

Information on how to apply is available at: https://chrispattersonmemorial.org/performing-arts-award/

In lieu of teacher signatures on the Awards Endorsement Form, students may email their instructor asking for confirmation of their participation and then print and include a copy of the teacher's response email. If there are questions, please email us at: hello@ChrisPattersonMemorial.org

UPDATE:

Our Butterbraid due date for order forms and money was scheduled for Tuesday March 17th with delivery on March 24th. We plan to continue the sale and these dates but would like you to send a PHOTO of your order form to Jamie Schambach at the number listed on your form, 630-212-3951 by March 17th.

The pickup will still be held on March 24th but an alternate location. If that day does not work for you, another time can be arranged. We will post about pickup locations as the date gets closer. If your child had already submitted their Butterbraid order to their teacher, please text Jamie at the number above and we will make arrangements to get it.

ALL MONEY WILL BE TURNED IN AT PICKUP on 3/24. Please let us know if you have any questions, and just a reminder, if your middle school student sells 10 or more butterbraids they are eligible for a free treble K t-shirt!!!

Volunteers needed at KHS... you don't have to be a band parent or even know how to sew, if you're free today (8/1) @3p, Friday (8/2) @3p, Monday (8/5) @12p and @5p, and/or Wednesday (8/7) @12p and @5p. ADDED THURSDAY @5p.. we need you!! Meet us in the band room.

It's band uniform fitting time and the more help we have helping the kids try on their uniforms the faster they can get back out on the marching field to practice. We have current and past parents that will help you so if you're free please come and help!!

If you do have some sewing skills but aren't able to volunteer during these days please let us know because the uniform moms could always use extra help.

Congratulations to Blaine and Sam for being chosen by the KHS band to be this years Louis Armstrong Jazz and the John Philip Sousa award recipients. The students are chosen by their peers and by Mr. Puckett. The awards were awarded at the Senior Music Awards.

The Louis Armstrong Award is the top senior jazz award and it is given out in recognition of outstanding musical achievement and an incredible dedication to the program.

John Philip Sousa is an award that honors the top student in a high-school band and recognizes superior musicianship and outstanding dedication
